1778516622244747	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvAQ		item.create	bn-ldd	{"description":"Foundational slice: define UsageEvent, Source, TokenCounts, ModelSlug. Stand up the asupersync runtime entry point. Implement the Claude reader (~/.claude/projects/<cwd>/*.jsonl). Vendor a LiteLLM pricing snapshot and the cost math. Render one month of Claude usage as the unsubsidized-cost table described in notes/plan.md §2. Done = 'cargo run' prints a monthly table for the current month using real ~/.claude data.","kind":"goal","size":"l","title":"M1: Core types + Claude reader + monthly output (foundation)"}	blake3:-q6tAxqadyvKeymJlzQWyxSq9-4Z41dVho-hB5ZypM4
1778516630386071	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvAg		item.create	bn-1gn	{"description":"Two more local readers normalising into UsageEvent. Pi: read ~/.pi/agent/sessions/session-index.sqlite (fall back to walkdir over <encoded-cwd>/*.jsonl), parse assistant messages where 'usage' is present (input/output/cacheRead/cacheWrite + provider + model). Codex: read ~/.codex/sessions/YYYY/MM/DD/rollout-*.jsonl with the cumulative state machine: session_meta resets, turn_context switches active model, token_count emits a delta (current minus previous, clamp negatives to 0). Both feed the same Sink as M1.","kind":"goal","size":"m","title":"M2: Pi + Codex readers"}	blake3:68JDKsi53RPHcwwyvWWzTbghcS4Hylf0RksLWBpoiiQ
1778516633420915	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvAw		item.create	bn-19m	{"description":"Gemini: walk ~/.gemini/tmp/<hash>/chats/session-*.json, pull usageMetadata.{promptTokenCount,candidatesTokenCount,cachedContentTokenCount,thoughtsTokenCount} per message; project column is hash[..8]. OpenCode: open ~/.local/share/opencode/opencode.db with SQLITE_OPEN_READONLY, stream message rows in created order (tokens_input/output/reasoning/cache_read/cache_write + model_id + provider_id). Legacy ~/.local/share/opencode/storage/message/<sid>/*.json fallback only when DB missing. If DB is locked, warn and skip.","kind":"goal","size":"m","title":"M3: Gemini + OpenCode readers"}	blake3:FS6lN69nUt0d_G299xplm4oT-_BNVAqwCLQE_1Q8GBQ
1778516636534307	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvBA		item.create	bn-6a7	{"description":"Use asupersync's HttpClientBuilder with tls + tls-webpki-roots. Fetch GET /api/v1/activity?date=YYYY-MM-DD for each of the last 30 UTC days, plus /api/v1/credits for the running balance. Auth from RECKON_OPENROUTER_KEY → OPENROUTER_API_KEY → ~/.config/reckon/config.toml. On 401 print 'Management API key required' with the settings URL. Map prompt_tokens→input, completion_tokens→output, reasoning_tokens→reasoning; keep upstream 'usage' (USD) alongside our computed unsubsidized cost for sanity-checking. dedup_key = openrouter:{date}:{endpoint_id}.","kind":"goal","size":"m","title":"M4: OpenRouter integration (/activity + /credits)"}	blake3:YGvZ6qy2Oajc3DrCQbM4R8RDU6hyupJArXJQq51PpM8
1778516639530034	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvBQ		item.create	bn-dcp	{"description":"Cache at ~/.cache/reckon/index.sqlite with the two tables in notes/plan.md §8: source_files(source, path, mtime_ns, size_bytes, last_offset) and events(source, dedup_key, month, model, provider, project, input, output, cache_read, cache_write, reasoning). JSONL readers resume from last_offset on warm runs; OpenCode queries WHERE created > last_max. OpenRouter never trusts the cache (30-day window). Cost is computed at display time, not stored — so refreshing pricing re-prices history without re-scanning. Done = second invocation under 200ms on a year of data.","kind":"goal","size":"m","title":"M5: SQLite cache/index for warm runs"}	blake3:fbkyZBBftAP_suXCSFu_0e0rjFvKE2UBylsVE35hmWo
1778516641815812	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvBg		item.create	bn-25e	{"description":"Fetch LiteLLM model_prices_and_context_window.json on first run and every 7 days, cache at ~/.cache/reckon/pricing.json. --offline disables refresh. Vendored fallback at crates/reckon-core/assets/pricing-fallback.json guarantees fresh-install --offline still costs major models correctly. xtask 'cargo xtask vendor-pricing' re-snapshots the fallback file. No other network traffic; no telemetry, ever.","kind":"goal","size":"s","title":"M6: Pricing auto-refresh + --offline"}	blake3:jawj9qXHCfXpMjld14qdL9gusCR-ytQbs5JEVYBQfsU
