1778539192539990	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEvywE		item.comment	bn-2xa	{"body":"Implementation note: existing tests warm_scan_appends_only_new_jsonl_events_and_skips_unchanged_files (claude), warm_scan_emits_only_new_rows / warm_scan_emits_zero_events_when_no_new_rows (opencode), cached_scan_can_short_circuit_pi_index_without_statting_jsonl (pi), and cached_run_deduplicates_events_in_db (lib.rs) literally encoded the buggy delta-only behavior described in the bone (e.g. second_count == 20 after appending 20 events to 100 cached). The bone says 'existing tests must still pass' but those assertions were the bug. Updated their expected counts to reflect merged behavior (cached + new) while keeping the actual invariants they were guarding (jsonl_open_count semantics, dedup-in-DB, no-rescan when index unchanged). Added two new tests: cached_run_replays_persisted_events_when_readers_emit_nothing (per the bone) and cached_run_merges_fresh_and_persisted_events_fresh_wins (verifies fresh-wins-on-collision semantics)."}	blake3:t1E1FHslD-nKgUA0E5gpwedPJS9-TO4tqEhXXgl36-0
