1778587521545486	reckon-dev	itc:v3:AWLk8kz5M8ySZQAAAAAAQevVvre1WgAAAAEv3QE		item.create	bn-2rx	{"description":"**Problem:** Pi and OpenCode rows that should carry real cost are showing `$0`. Root cause is THREE compounding mismatches between what the readers emit and what the pricing loader indexes. Magnitudes affected on this machine: opencode `openai/gpt-5.4` April: 91M input + 2.8M output + 950M cache_read tokens, currently \\$0 (should be ~\\$500). Opencode `anthropic/claude-opus-4-5` Jan: 800M cache_read tokens, currently \\$0 (should be ~\\$1200). Multiply across months and models, this is several thousand dollars missing.\n\n**The three mismatches:**\n\n1. **Bare pricing key without provider prefix.** Pricing-fallback has `\"gpt-5.5\"` (bare). The reader (opencode) emits `openai/gpt-5.5` (provider-prefixed). The pricing loader indexes the bare key as `ModelSlug(\"gpt-5.5\")`. There's no `openrouter/openai/gpt-5.5` variant in pricing to bridge the two — only older `gpt-5.2` family has those. Same for `gpt-5.4`, `gpt-5.3-codex`, `gpt-5.3-codex-spark`.\n\n2. **Family-normalization missing for OpenCode + older Anthropic models.** `model_map::opencode_canonical` simply does `format!(\"{provider}/{raw}\")`. OpenCode's `modelID` for older Anthropic is `claude-opus-4-5` (no date), yielding slug `anthropic/claude-opus-4-5` (dash). Pricing has `openrouter/anthropic/claude-opus-4.5` (dot) → canonicalizes to `anthropic/claude-opus-4.5`. Mismatch. Same for `claude-sonnet-4-5`, `claude-haiku-4-5`.\n\n3. **Pi provider strings aren't vendor names.** Pi records `provider: \"google-gemini-cli\"` and `provider: \"openai-codex\"` for some models. `model_map::pi_canonical` does `format!(\"{provider}/{normalized}\")` so it emits `google-gemini-cli/gemini-3-pro-preview` and `openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex`. Pricing knows `google/...` and `openai/...`.\n\n**Scope:**\n\n- `crates/reckon-core/src/pricing.rs` (primary)\n- `crates/reckon-core/src/model_map.rs` (secondary)\n\n**Approach:**\n\na) **Pricing loader: cross-index bare keys under their litellm_provider.** When `canonical_slug` produces a `ModelSlug(raw)` (no slash), the loader should also insert the entry under `ModelSlug(\"{litellm_provider}/{raw}\")` if `litellm_provider` is present. This makes `gpt-5.5` queryable as either `gpt-5.5` or `openai/gpt-5.5`. Implementation: in `load_pricing_from_str`, after computing the canonical slug, also compute a provider-prefixed alias when the canonical is bare AND `entry.litellm_provider` is set AND vendor normalization is meaningful (use `normalize_vendor` to coalesce `vertex_ai` → `google`, `gemini` → `google`, `vertex_ai-language-models` → `google`, etc.). Keep both entries in the map.\n\nb) **Extend `claude_canonical` to cover 4.5 families.** Add `(\"claude-opus-4-5\",   \"anthropic/claude-opus-4.5\"), (\"claude-sonnet-4-5\", \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5\"), (\"claude-haiku-4-5\",  \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5\")`. (The haiku-4.5 entry already exists for the family literal; verify exact ordering doesn't collide.)\n\nc) **Route opencode anthropic models through claude_canonical.** Update `opencode_canonical` so when `provider == \"anthropic\"`, it runs the raw through `claude_canonical` first; only fall back to the current `format!(\"{provider}/{raw}\")` if claude_canonical returns None.\n\nd) **Pi: normalize provider strings.** Add a small `normalize_pi_provider` helper inside `pi_canonical`:\n- `\"google-gemini-cli\"` → `\"google\"`\n- `\"openai-codex\"` → `\"openai\"`\n- otherwise return as-is.\n\nAlso, when the (normalized) provider is `anthropic`, route raw through `claude_canonical` exactly like opencode.\n\n**Acceptance:**\n\n- `cargo test --workspace` passes.\n- Add unit tests in `pricing.rs`: `load_pricing_from_str` includes both `gpt-5.5` AND `openai/gpt-5.5` keys after loading a synthetic entry with `litellm_provider: \"openai\"`.\n- Add unit tests in `model_map.rs`:\n  - `canonical(Source::OpenCode, \"claude-opus-4-5\", Some(\"anthropic\"))` → `anthropic/claude-opus-4.5`.\n  - `canonical(Source::Pi, \"gemini-3-pro-preview\", Some(\"google-gemini-cli\"))` → `google/gemini-3-pro-preview`.\n  - `canonical(Source::Pi, \"gpt-5.3-codex\", Some(\"openai-codex\"))` → `openai/gpt-5.3-codex`.\n  - `canonical(Source::Pi, \"claude-haiku-4-5\", Some(\"anthropic\"))` continues to return `anthropic/claude-haiku-4.5` (no regression).\n- Smoke run after fresh cache: `cargo run --bin reckon` should show non-zero cost for: opencode openai/gpt-5.4, opencode openai/gpt-5.5, opencode openai/gpt-5.3-codex, opencode anthropic/claude-opus-4.5, pi google/gemini-3-pro-preview, pi openai/gpt-5.3-codex. The \"priced at \\$0 (no pricing data)\" warning should drop a substantial fraction of its entries.\n\n**Out of scope:**\n\n- `<synthetic>` model (auto-compaction subagents, all zeros — file a separate cosmetic bone if it bothers anyone).\n- Ollama local models (`ollama/gemma4`, `ollama/glm-4.7-flash`, etc.) — these are genuinely free; leave them at \\$0.\n- `opencode/big-pickle` and other internal opencode codenames — unknown pricing, leave at \\$0.","kind":"bug","labels":["pricing","correctness","opencode","pi"],"size":"m","title":"Fix $0 pricing for opencode/pi: provider-prefix indexing + family normalization"}	blake3:HQNM15t5QFm6_Z_LDAkGPsdSpNW2huRY3Q_xriVAeMk
